Jump Directly to the U-IT Functional Needs and A-IT Solutions

 

 

COGNOS AS AN A-IT SOLUTION:

With the increased focus on removing all Unauthorized Information Technology (U-IT) from the DFAS network, Cognos Analytics is an Authorized IT (A-IT) platform of choice to replace reporting and visualization applications. Cognos is a tool accredited within the information system boundary for the individual systems using it as a report/query tool. The migration of U-IT applications to Cognos is one solution to move processes to an A-IT platform with an Authority to Operate (ATO).  

Cognos Analytics provides an accredited platform on which to build an A-IT solution that includes live or scheduled data retrieval and processing to create reports, dashboards, or other types of information visualizations and analysis while safeguarding sensitive data using FIPS 140-2 encryption for both data-in-transit and data-at-rest.

 

COGNOS IS USED FOR:

Cognos Analytics is an enterprise Business Analytics platform for governed data discovery and reporting that eases the process of creating reports and dashboards, giving business analysts and citizen developers the freedom to do it on their own. The user experience is designed for business professionals to easily prepare, create and visualize content using artificial intelligence and natural language tools to guide them when using both enterprise and personal stores of data.

 

IS COGNOS GOING AWAY?

Cognos, as a desktop application has been in use at DFAS since the agency’s inception. The desktop version (v7.5) has been replaced with an updated, modern web version (starting at v11.1).

Cognos Analytics is a new technology with the power of IBM Watson behind it. This updated version has full support from IBM and DFAS and is not going away. All future utilization will be through the web version.

 

IS COGNOS A GOOD FIT?

Cognos is a robust web-based analytics tool that incorporates extensive and customizable data visualizations with descriptive analytics (what happened), diagnostic analytics (why did it happen), and predictive analytics (what will happen next). Cognos is used at DFAS today to run simple queries, complex reports, executive dashboards, and live presentation-style storyboards. Cognos connects directly to system data sources and allows importing of user data to give the capability for IT, Ops, and any DFAS Customer to have immediate access to live reports that combine data from these disparate sources.

 

Cognos can be utilized for:

· Workgroup task planning

· Directorate-level reporting

· Executive briefing presentations

· Input to financial reports

· Financial reconciliations

· Audit performance to goals

· Productivity/financial trend analyses

· Fraud/abuse identification

· Making complex data available to decision-makers in a friendly/digestible format.

Cognos may be the right solution when answers to several of these questions are ‘Yes’.

1. Is your data stored in a DFAS-owned system or in Excel/CSV files?

a. Cognos has the ability to query DFAS owned systems to provide real-time results without the need to transfer files from the source system.

b. Cognos has the ability to report based on uploaded Excel or CSV files which can be manually updated as often as you have a new copy.

2. Is there a need to limit access or to provide open access to all holders of a DoD CAC?

a. Should the application be locked down so it is limited to who can utilize and see the application and/or who can make authorized changes?

b. Should report outputs be made available to any person with a DoD CAC?

3. Is there a need for segregation of duties?

a. Cognos has the ability to set up different roles to allow for different users to have different access to content or to tools, based on needs

4. Is there a need for data-level security?

a. Cognos encrypts all data when uploaded

b. Cognos assists in enforcing row-level security from a back-end database

5. Is there a need for automation to execute on a schedule?

a. Cognos can be set up to run on regular schedules using automation, while also providing the means to run on demand as well.

6. Is there a need for multiple users to have the ability to run the project? For example:

a. If someone is on leave and a backup needs to run the project

b. If more than one person in the office has responsibilities and needs to have access to run on demand to review for changes/updates since the project was last executed

7. Does the application require access or change auditing?

a. Cognos automatically records audit information such as who accesses, runs, copies, changes, etc. any object within the Cognos platform. Audit logs can be provided on request or scheduled to be sent regularly if needed.

b. Cognos can also send a report containing who has access to an application’s content and can be scheduled to be sent regularly as an audit artifact or for manual review

8. Is there a need for data analytics, simple data transformation, or data visualization?

a. Cognos data analytics allows for users to seamlessly automate distribution of reports, display metrics reporting, and display live/real-time data.

b. Cognos data transformation allows for users to utilize data consolidation, letter/report creation, interface, and data normalization.

c. Cognos utilizes robust data visualization methods to display results of reports and queries.

9. Would leaders like to utilize dashboards showing summary information?

a. Cognos dashboards contain at-a-glance summary information that can be drilled down to provide more in-depth details.

10. Is there a need for the ability to slice/dice data based on various categories, drilling down through levels of detail?

a. Cognos Cubes are a multidimensional representation of data with pre-calculated totals, summaries, or aggregations.

COGNOS CAPABILITIES INCLUDE:

1. Cognos is an authorized IT (A-IT) solution

· Cognos has an ATO and has been vetted to be an approved IT solution

· Audit information is stored automatically and can be made available for each application if needed

2. Multiple users can access, run, and view the results

· Cognos has a folder that allows many users to access and run reports and queries, simultaneously

· Cognos’ security capabilities can be as simple or complex as required

3. System Connections

· Cognos is able to connect to DFAS owned systems with any type of standard database layout such as RDBMS (Oracle, SQL Server) or IDMS (Mainframe)

4. Data Analytics

· Cognos allows for users to seamlessly automate distribution of reports, display metrics reporting, and contains live/real-time data. Cognos utilizes descriptive analytics (what happened), diagnostic analytics (why did it happen), and predictive analytics (what will happen next)

· Analytics functions such as those found in Excel Analysis Toolpak and other analytics tools are available in Cognos

5. Data Utilization

· Cognos data transformation allows for users to utilize data consolidation, letter/report creation, interface, and data normalization

· Cognos offers the ability to share and embed content into webpages like SharePoint

6. Data Visualization

· Cognos utilizes data visualization to display results of reports and queries on dashboards, reports, storyboards, and cubes

· Dynamic dashboards are interactive and allow drag and drop data to create auto-generated visuals, drill down for more detailing, and offer the ability share through email

· Storyboards allow for users to tell a story with their data similar to the idea of an automated PowerPoint presentation

· Cubes, or other Online Analytic Processing (OLAP) data sources, can be used as a data source for reports or can be accessed directly by a cube viewer. Cubes, similar to the idea of pivot tables in excel, leverages pre-calculated aggregates to allow slicing and dicing of data based on categories.

 

COGNOS LIMITATIONS INCLUDE:

· Data Input such as:

a. Active Workflow Management –Cognos would not be a good fit for workflow information that is constantly/actively needing updated

b. Ticketing Input and Management – Cognos is not intended for users to input new data for tickets or modify existing tickets

c. Input Forms for Metrics or Comments – Cognos is not intended to be utilized for input forms

 

COGNOS PROCESS:

Currently, DFAS’ enterprise license makes the Cognos available for ALL DFAS employees. Any employee can request access to use the Cognos Self Service platform which allows business analysts or citizen developers to create content. Follow these steps if you believe Cognos Self Service is a good fit for you.

1. User identifies need to migrate U-IT application to Cognos Self Service

2. User begins taking available Cognos Analytics training by logging into the ‘My DFAS Training Dashboard’ on the DFAS Portal, and search for “Cognos”. There are 7 self-paced on-line IBM Cognos Analytics training courses available.

3. User fills out a DD2875 with needed role(s) and DoD ID and routes it for the approval process. The user should select a capability role and at least one folder/object access role.

a. The DD2875 template has a list of capability roles with descriptions for each

b. A list of current Cognos Self Service folder/object access roles can be found here: https://selfserve-ba.dfas.mil/DEV/ReportAdmin/Self-ServiceUserRoles-en-us.xlsx

c. If the user is unsure which capability role(s) to request, or if they are requesting a new folder be created, they can contact the Cognos Development Team (dfas.indianapolis-in.zte.mbx.corporate-services-business-analyti@mail.mil)

4. The DD2875 approval process includes a signature from the user, their supervisor, Security (SSO), ELAN group (dfas.indianapolis-in.ztd.mbx.iao-indy-new@mail.mil), and Cognos Analytics Administrators (dfas.indianapolis-in.zta.list.cin-bi-admin@mail.mil). The Cognos Analytics Administrators provision the role and notify the user via email.

5. Once the secured folder is set up, users will set up a connection to a DFAS owned system or upload excel sheets or CSV files into Cognos

a. To create a new connection between Cognos and a DFAS owned system, users and Cognos Admins (dfas.indianapolis-in.zta.list.cin-bi-admin@mail.mil) complete a DD2875 and sends it to be processed.

b. For existing connections between Cognos and a DFAS owned system, users will need to be added to a Cognos role to allow utilization of the connection.

c. For assistance with Cognos to DFAS owned system connections contact the Cognos Development Team (dfas.indianapolis-in.zte.mbx.corporate-services-business-analyti@mail.mil)

6. Once the connection is set up, users with the appropriate roles can start creating reports and queries

 

U-IT FUNCTIONAL NEEDS AND A-IT SOLUTIONS

Existing U-IT applications within the operational areas across DFAS were evaluated for functional need requirements. Six major categories of functional needs were identified: Workload Management, Workflow, Ticketing, Data Reconciliation, Data Analytics, and Data Transformation.

The current five A-IT solutions (ACL (DTPAT) Server, Cognos, SharePoint, Oracle Apex, and Advana) provided scores to reflect the software’s ability to meet specific functional needs. Scores were obtained in three areas: capability, skill set, and coding. The scores are intended to serve as a guide during the process of exploring possible A-IT solutions. Higher scores indicated increased feasibility that the A-IT solution will be a suitable option to meet the functional needs.
